<% layout('layouts/boilerplate') %>

<div class="row mb-3">
  <div class="d-none d-md-block col-4 my-auto">
    <figure class="text-center">
      <blockquote class="blockquote" style="color:#c2272d">
        <p class="fs-2">By Live Role Players,<br />For Live Role Players</p>
      </blockquote>
      <figcaption class="blockquote-footer">
        <cite title="Source Title">Almost Every LRP Organiser</cite>
      </figcaption>
    </figure>
  </div>
  <div class="col lead text-center border-start ps-4">
    <p>There is no denying that the root of Live Role Play is as a community hobby. Most trace back to university and gaming groups that wanted to branch away from the traditional table top gaming.</p>
    <p>In recent years that ideal has shifted slightly and now a large number of highly successful commercial event organisers make it difficult (not deliberately) for smaller systems to compete. So we wanted to bring back that age old mantra used by so many; <br /><i>"By Live Role Players, For Live Role Players"</i></p>
    <p>One of the largest hurdles faced by LRP Event Organisers is the logistics of getting attendees to their events. The myriad of complications from taking payments, and protecting your guests data have made running a Live Role Play event a minefield.</p>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="d-grid gap-2 mb-3 mt-5 mx-md-5">
  <a href="/organisers/register" class="mx-md-5 btn text-light" style="background-color: #c2272d; border-color: #c2272d;">
    <h3 class="mt-2">Click Here To Register Your Event System</h3>
  </a>
</div>
<div class="row py-4 mt-md-5">
  <div id="advertising" class="col text-center px-5">
    <div class="fs-2 text-center mb-3">
      Advertising
    </div>
    <p>Advertising your event to reach as many potential players as possible is difficult, and takes a lot of work.</p>
    <p>Here are some of the benefits we offer to advertise your event.</p>
    <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
      <li class="list-group-item" data-bs-toggle="popover" data-bs-placement="top" data-bs-trigger="hover" data-bs-content="List your event on our front page, as well as having a dedicated event page to share your crucial information">Advertise your event <b>FOR FREE</b></li>
      <li class="list-group-item" data-bs-toggle="popover" data-bs-placement="top" data-bs-trigger="hover" data-bs-content="Event dates, location, ticket prices, and contact details are always placed in the same place so players can find them easily">Highlight key event information</li>
      <li class="list-group-item" data-bs-toggle="popover" data-bs-placement="top" data-bs-trigger="hover" data-bs-content="Our website has been carefully designed to be just as functional on mobile as it is on a PC">PC & mobile friendly adverts</li>
      <li class="list-group-item" data-bs-toggle="popover" data-bs-placement="top" data-bs-trigger="hover" data-bs-content="Users have the option to sign up to updates about your systems events, automatically getting notified when new events are available">Automatic e-mail marketing</li>
      <li class="list-group-item" data-bs-toggle="popover" data-bs-placement="top" data-bs-trigger="hover" data-bs-content="If you have your own Discord server, you can use Discord Webhooks to automatically share when your events are advertised">Automatic publishing via Discord Webhooks</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div id="booking" class="col text-center px-5">
    <div class="fs-2 text-center mb-3">
      Booking
    </div>
    <p>Keeping track of your bookings, payments, and confirming receipt of those to your players is a huge logistical nightmare.</p>
    <p>These are some of the ways we take that pressure away.</p>
    <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
      <li class="list-group-item" data-bs-toggle="popover" data-bs-placement="top" data-bs-trigger="hover" data-bs-content="Registering by using their existing logins makes your players lives easier. We're always looking at other integrations to improve this further">Users can register by E-mail, Google, or Facebook Accounts</li>
      <li class="list-group-item" data-bs-toggle="popover" data-bs-placement="top" data-bs-trigger="hover" data-bs-content="Being able to book and pay for their events in one place will help give your players confidence in your system">Players can book and pay for your event online</li>
      <li class="list-group-item" data-bs-toggle="popover" data-bs-placement="top" data-bs-trigger="hover" data-bs-content="Having an easy log of who has booked and paid is a critical part of event logistics">View who has booked and paid at a glance</li>
      <li class="list-group-item" data-bs-toggle="popover" data-bs-placement="top" data-bs-trigger="hover" data-bs-content="Not everyone has access to the internet, so we've made it easy to add manual bookings for your players">Easily manage manual bookings and payments</li>
      <li class="list-group-item" data-bs-toggle="popover" data-bs-placement="top" data-bs-trigger="hover" data-bs-content="You control when your tickets are on sale, and when they stop being available.">Fine control over booking deadlines</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>
<hr class="text-muted">
<div class="row py-4 mt-3">
  <div id="finance-logistics" class="col text-center px-5">
    <div class="fs-2 text-center mb-3">
      Financial Logistics
    </div>
    <p>Site fees, insurance, PayPal fees, to name just a few! Managing the costs related to running an event can leave you buried in spreadsheets.</p>
    <p>Let us tackle the maths and break it down it for you</p>
    <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
      <li class="list-group-item" data-bs-toggle="popover" data-bs-placement="top" data-bs-trigger="hover" data-bs-content="Easily see how your income compares to your expected income">Quickly see confirmed and pending income</li>
      <li class="list-group-item" data-bs-toggle="popover" data-bs-placement="top" data-bs-trigger="hover" data-bs-content="Record your major event costs (e.g. Site Fee or Insurance) and it will automatically calculate your event profit & loss">Record your critical event costs</li>
      <li class="list-group-item" data-bs-toggle="popover" data-bs-placement="top" data-bs-trigger="hover" data-bs-content="PayPal always take's its cut, but how much of your event is taken by it? We've worked it out for you and can be seen quickly by managing your event.">Easily view charges for player bookings via PayPal</li>
      <li class="list-group-item" data-bs-toggle="popover" data-bs-placement="top" data-bs-trigger="hover" data-bs-content="Working out your breakeven points is difficult, by giving us your event costs we can work it out for you!">Visual displays of breakeven points</li>
      <li class="list-group-item" data-bs-toggle="popover" data-bs-placement="top" data-bs-trigger="hover" data-bs-content="We all hope our event will sell out, so we show you exactly how much income you will have after your costs">See projected income on a fully booked event</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div id="event-logistics" class="col text-center px-5">
    <div class="fs-2 text-center mb-3">
      Event Logistics
    </div>
    <p>Getting bookings for your event is only the first step! Now you need a small library of paperwork to make your event function!</p>
    <p>We've hit the books already, so some of these should help you out.</p>
    <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
      <li class="list-group-item" data-bs-toggle="popover" data-bs-placement="top" data-bs-trigger="hover" data-bs-content="It's a simple thing, but keeping track of who is at your event can get the better of us all! Featuring sign in and sign out options foreach day of your event, our sheet hopes to keep it simple">Sign-In sheets for your event</li>
      <li class="list-group-item" data-bs-toggle="popover" data-bs-placement="top" data-bs-trigger="hover" data-bs-content="Whilst this feature is still growing, you can scan your players tickets to confirm they are valid for your event. We hope to build this into a sign in system in the future.">Ticket scanning (if your venue has an internet connection!)</li>
      <li class="list-group-item" data-bs-toggle="popover" data-bs-placement="top" data-bs-trigger="hover" data-bs-content="Keeping track of your attendee's catering choices often requires outside services. We've included it as standard!">Catering choices and reporting</li>
      <li class="list-group-item" data-bs-toggle="popover" data-bs-placement="top" data-bs-trigger="hover" data-bs-content="If you're handling your catering directly, you'll need to be able to pass this info to your caterer. A covered confidential report keeps your players information safe from prying eyes">Confidential Dietary / Allergy PDF reports</li>
      <li class="list-group-item" data-bs-toggle="popover" data-bs-placement="top" data-bs-trigger="hover" data-bs-content="Some players may have emergency medical needs, and in an emergency you need them easily to hand. A covered confidential report keeps your players information safe from prying eyes">Confidential First Aid / Medical PDF reports</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>
<hr class="text-muted">
<div class="row py-4 mt-3">
  <div id="users" class="col text-center px-5">
    <div class="fs-2 text-center mb-3">
      User Benefits
    </div>
    <p>This is all about the players, so we need to make it as easy as possible for them to get to your event.</p>
    <p>This is how we are making that happen</p>
    <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
      <li class="list-group-item" data-bs-toggle="popover" data-bs-placement="top" data-bs-trigger="hover" data-bs-content="Registering by using their existing logins makes your players lives easier. We're always looking at other integrations to improve this further">Users can register by E-mail, Google, or Facebook Accounts</li>
      <li class="list-group-item" data-bs-toggle="popover" data-bs-placement="top" data-bs-trigger="hover" data-bs-content="Updating their details in one place, means they can make the change for all the systems that use us at once">Easily manage and update their own details</li>
      <li class="list-group-item" data-bs-toggle="popover" data-bs-placement="top" data-bs-trigger="hover" data-bs-content="Rather than chasing through e-mails for event bookings, we provide one place to check and review their event bookings">View all their event bookings on one page</li>
      <li class="list-group-item" data-bs-toggle="popover" data-bs-placement="top" data-bs-trigger="hover" data-bs-content="Sometimes you only want to go to an event if your friend is going to. We give that choice to each player to decide if they want to share that they are attending">Choose if they want to display their attendance to your event</li>
      <li class="list-group-item" data-bs-toggle="popover" data-bs-placement="top" data-bs-trigger="hover" data-bs-content="If they want to buy a ticket for someone else, they can! Tickets can be transferred to other users with ease (but only if an event hasn't sold out!)">Gift an event booking to another user</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div id="your-system" class="col text-center px-5">
    <div class="fs-2 text-center mb-3">
      Your Event System
    </div>
    <p>You've spent a long time creating your game. How do you use a third party like us and still retain your own identity?</p>
    <p>How about we give you your own space</p>
    <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
      <li class="list-group-item" data-bs-toggle="popover" data-bs-placement="top" data-bs-trigger="hover" data-bs-content="This gives you your own space to link your players to that will only display your events.">Dedicated page for each event system, showing only your events</li>
      <li class="list-group-item" data-bs-toggle="popover" data-bs-placement="top" data-bs-trigger="hover" data-bs-content="We allow an Event System to have multiple hosts, maybe you have nations/clans/other that can host events in your world">Add your own event system, event host, and event logos</li>
      <li class="list-group-item" data-bs-toggle="popover" data-bs-placement="top" data-bs-trigger="hover" data-bs-content="Whatever terms you have for people attending your events, it's important that they can be seen and agreed to before booking. We give you that option">Require your own terms & conditions for attending your events</li>
      <li class="list-group-item" data-bs-toggle="popover" data-bs-placement="top" data-bs-trigger="hover" data-bs-content="We require a character name to book any event, but do you track a player id? Maybe you want to know their characters homeland? These are options you can control - as well as if that information is required to book">Set player and character information that is unique to your system</li>
      <li class="list-group-item" data-bs-toggle="popover" data-bs-placement="top" data-bs-trigger="hover" data-bs-content="Managing an event is often too much work for one person, so we provide the option to let other people manage your events. And you can control it!">Control your own system admins and who can create your events</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>
<hr class="text-muted">
